[Sighs] Can't.

251
00:13:21,051 --> 00:13:23,345
I'm in Alabama.

252
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:27,140
Oh... my God.

253
00:13:28,934 --> 00:13:29,935
Yeah.

254
00:14:24,406 --> 00:14:26,742
[Birds chirping]

255
00:14:29,077 --> 00:14:30,412
[Barks]

256
00:14:32,581 --> 00:14:34,917
[Barks]

257
00:14:37,252 --> 00:14:42,132
[Barking slowly]

258
00:14:49,473 --> 00:14:52,017
Aw, he's loud,
but he don't bite.

259
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:53,560
Come on, shut up, hound!

260
00:14:53,644 --> 00:14:54,686
Lie down.

261
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:56,939
Go on, stay.

262
00:14:57,022 --> 00:14:59,274
Now, how can I help you?

263
00:14:59,358 --> 00:15:02,444
Well, for starters, you can get
your stubborn ass down here

264
00:15:02,528 --> 00:15:03,946
and give me a divorce.

265
00:15:06,657 --> 00:15:08,951
...[Thud]
...[Groans]

266
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:10,702
[Sighs] Come on,
Jake, I mean it.

267
00:15:10,786 --> 00:15:12,120
The joke's over.

268
00:15:12,204 --> 00:15:14,081
Let's just finish this.
I've got a plane to catch.

269
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:19,378
You're shittin' me, right?

270
00:15:19,461 --> 00:15:21,964
You know, I've never actually
understood that expression,

271
00:15:22,047 --> 00:15:23,966
but, no,
I'm not "shitting" you.

272
00:15:24,007 --> 00:15:27,427
Look, it's even got
these idiot-proof tabs

273
00:15:27,469 --> 00:15:28,595
to make it easy.

274
00:15:28,637 --> 00:15:30,848
There's one copy for me,
one copy for you,

275
00:15:30,931 --> 00:15:32,641
and one copy
for the lawyers.

276
00:15:32,724 --> 00:15:35,769
[Exhales sharply]

277
00:15:38,021 --> 00:15:39,273
What? Speak!

278
00:15:39,314 --> 00:15:40,274
[Slow barking resumes]

279
00:15:40,315 --> 00:15:43,944
You show up here
after 7 years

280
00:15:43,986 --> 00:15:47,447
without so much as a "Hey,
there, Jake, remember me...

281
00:15:47,489 --> 00:15:49,658
your wife?"

282
00:15:49,741 --> 00:15:52,786
Or a "Hi, honey.
Lookin' good.

283
00:15:52,870 --> 00:15:54,830
How's the family?"

284
00:15:54,913 --> 00:15:56,748
You expect me to tell you
you look good?

285
00:15:56,832 --> 00:15:59,168
Did they run out of soap down at
the Piggly Wiggly since I left?

286
00:15:59,251 --> 00:16:00,294
[Slow barking continues]

287
00:16:00,377 --> 00:16:03,088
They laugh at that up north
or wherever it is you been?

288
00:16:03,172 --> 00:16:04,798
You knew where I was.

289
00:16:04,882 --> 00:16:07,176
And don't even pretend you spent
all this time missing me.

290
00:16:07,259 --> 00:16:09,011
Oh, I missed you,
all right.

291
00:16:09,094 --> 00:16:11,763
But at this range,
my aim is bound to improve.

292
00:16:11,847 --> 00:16:13,807
Is that a threat?

293
00:16:13,891 --> 00:16:16,310
I've got a lawyer
who charges $350 an hour.

294
00:16:16,351 --> 00:16:19,146
He billed me every time
you sent these papers back.

295
00:16:19,188 --> 00:16:21,190
Well, I'm glad to see
you finally got the message.

296
00:16:21,231 --> 00:16:23,108
...Shut up, Bear!
...Shut up, Bryant!

297
00:16:23,192 --> 00:16:25,986
[Barks, groans]

298
00:16:26,028 --> 00:16:28,864
What happened to Bear?

299
00:16:28,947 --> 00:16:31,450
He died.

300
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:33,118
You weren't here.

301
00:16:34,536 --> 00:16:35,954
What are you doing?!

302
00:16:36,038 --> 00:16:37,414
Leavin'. You done it.

303
00:16:37,497 --> 00:16:39,833
You should recognize
the gesture.

304
00:16:39,875 --> 00:16:43,170
Could we just try to keep this
as civilized as possible?

305
00:16:43,212 --> 00:16:45,797
Please sign these papers
so I can go home.

306
00:16:45,881 --> 00:16:47,508
What do you know from home?

307
00:16:47,591 --> 00:16:50,552
Hell, I bet your folks don't
even know you're in town.

308
00:16:50,594 --> 00:16:52,179
That's my business.

309
00:16:52,262 --> 00:16:55,390
Honey, those people are
the only family you got.

310
00:16:55,474 --> 00:16:56,808
Don't you "honey" me,
honey!

311
00:16:56,892 --> 00:17:00,020
Get your butt back in that car,
you drive over and see 'em,

312
00:17:00,103 --> 00:17:02,689
and then maybe we'll talk.

313
00:17:02,773 --> 00:17:03,899
[Screen door slams]

314
00:17:03,982 --> 00:17:06,777
Jake! You dumb, stubborn,
redneck hick!

315
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:09,112
The only reason you
won't sign these papers

316
00:17:09,196 --> 00:17:10,405
is 'cause I want you to!

317
00:17:10,489 --> 00:17:12,533
Wrong! The only reason
I ain't signin'

318
00:17:12,616 --> 00:17:16,703
is 'cause you've turned into
some hoity-toity Yankee bitch,

319
00:17:16,787 --> 00:17:20,332
and I'd like nothin' better
right now than to piss you off!

320
00:17:23,377 --> 00:17:26,463
[Grumbling]

321
00:17:30,801 --> 00:17:32,386
Unh!

322
00:17:34,096 --> 00:17:37,015
What are you doin' with
Mose Plydell's plane anyhow?!

323
00:17:37,099 --> 00:17:38,225
That's my business!

324
00:17:38,267 --> 00:17:40,394
...Fine!
...Fine!

325
00:17:45,774 --> 00:17:47,901
[Door locks]

326
00:17:54,658 --> 00:17:57,661
[Groans]
Divorce, my ass.

327
00:18:07,963 --> 00:18:09,756
[Groans softly]

328
00:18:14,052 --> 00:18:15,554
Hey, genius...

329
00:18:15,637 --> 00:18:18,098
[Sighs]

330
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:20,350
Next time you lock somebody out,

331
00:18:20,434 --> 00:18:23,437
make sure they don't know
where the spare key's hidden.

332
00:18:23,478 --> 00:18:27,441
Well, see, that's the thing
about Hide-A-Keys...

333
00:18:27,482 --> 00:18:31,445
it'd be nice if your wife
told you where it was!

334
00:18:31,486 --> 00:18:33,614
I'm not your wife, Jake.

335
00:18:33,655 --> 00:18:36,533
I'm just the first girl

336
00:18:36,617 --> 00:18:38,619
that climbed
in the back of your truck.

337
00:18:40,329 --> 00:18:44,291
But you're right...
I have changed.

338
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,919
I don't even know
that girl anymore.

339
00:18:47,002 --> 00:18:52,299
Well, then...
allow me to remind you.

340
00:18:59,723 --> 00:19:01,767
[Door slams]

341
00:19:01,850 --> 00:19:06,563
"Born into one of the wealthiest
families of Greenville, Alabama,

342
00:19:06,647 --> 00:19:10,317
her daddy's in cotton and
all that that implies."

343
00:19:10,359 --> 00:19:13,695
There's no listing for an
Earl Carmichael in Greenville.

344
00:19:13,779 --> 00:19:15,030
How about her local high school?

345
00:19:15,113 --> 00:19:18,325
No record of a Melanie
Carmichael attending... ever.

346
00:19:18,408 --> 00:19:22,371
Jesus! Whatever happened
to responsible journalism?

347
00:19:25,707 --> 00:19:28,043
There's something
wrong here.

348
00:19:28,126 --> 00:19:30,879
Why would my son
do this to me?

349
00:19:30,963 --> 00:19:32,923
Maybe he, um, loves her.

350
00:19:33,006 --> 00:19:34,049
Oh, please!

351
00:19:34,132 --> 00:19:36,051
This is classic rebound.

352
00:19:36,134 --> 00:19:38,720
He's still wounded from...
who was his last girlfriend?

353
00:19:38,804 --> 00:19:41,515
Whitney Truesdale,
lawyer, San Francisco.

354
00:19:41,598 --> 00:19:43,934
Yeah, well, there was
a match made in Heaven...

355
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:48,272
society, political family,
California...

356
00:19:48,355 --> 00:19:50,691
all those electoral votes.

357
00:19:50,774 --> 00:19:53,026
Get Andrew on the phone.

358
00:19:53,110 --> 00:19:56,572
Since we have a small window
for the Secretary of Housing,

359
00:19:56,655 --> 00:19:59,157
please hold your questions
until after the presentation.

360
00:19:59,241 --> 00:20:00,701
Gentlemen.

361
00:20:00,742 --> 00:20:02,411
Did you see the look
on my mom's face?

362
00:20:02,494 --> 00:20:04,079
I thought her head
was going to explode.

363
00:20:04,162 --> 00:20:05,455
Yeah, what did she say?

364
00:20:05,539 --> 00:20:07,416
That I should date women
like Melanie, not marry them.

365
00:20:07,499 --> 00:20:10,043
...That's harsh.
...That's Mom.

366
00:20:10,127 --> 00:20:11,628
...Thank you.
...Thanks a lot.

367
00:20:11,712 --> 00:20:13,463
We hope to have
the Bronx Children's Hospital

368
00:20:13,547 --> 00:20:15,424
...open by fall 2003.
...[Cellphone ringing]

369
00:20:15,507 --> 00:20:17,843
Oh, speak of the devil.
Hello?

370
00:20:17,926 --> 00:20:20,596
So, have you two lovebirds
set a date?

371
00:20:20,679 --> 00:20:22,139
I'm pleading the Fifth.

372
00:20:22,222 --> 00:20:24,433
Okay, fine, just try to keep
your secrets. I dare you.

373
00:20:24,516 --> 00:20:26,435
Oh, at least you sound like
you're in a better mood.

374
00:20:26,518 --> 00:20:28,312
My approval rating
went up 2 points.

375
00:20:28,395 --> 00:20:30,939
It seems the public likes
being reminded I am a mother.

376
00:20:31,023 --> 00:20:32,441
God, always running for office.

377
00:20:32,524 --> 00:20:35,736
I'm only thinking of you.
Say, um...

378
00:20:35,777 --> 00:20:38,405
do you happen to have
the Carmichaels' number

379
00:20:38,447 --> 00:20:40,741
down there in Greenville?

380
00:20:40,782 --> 00:20:43,577
I thought perhaps
I should introduce myself.

381
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:45,746
I would like to meet them first,
if you don't mind.

382
00:20:45,829 --> 00:20:48,582
You do realize the press
is going to be all over this.

383
00:20:48,665 --> 00:20:50,417
Happy couples don't sell.

384
00:20:50,459 --> 00:20:54,004
So if there are any skeletons
in her closet, Andrew,

385
00:20:54,087 --> 00:20:55,964
we need to know about them.

386
00:20:56,048 --> 00:20:59,051
[Indistinct talking
on police radio]

387
00:21:00,511 --> 00:21:02,137
You make clothes, right?

388
00:21:02,221 --> 00:21:04,973
I design them.
There's a big difference.

389
00:21:05,057 --> 00:21:07,476
Did you design anything
with stripes?

390
00:21:07,518 --> 00:21:10,437
...[Knock on door]
...You called the sheriff?!

391
00:21:10,479 --> 00:21:14,107
You know that old bastard
hates me!

392
00:21:14,149 --> 00:21:15,734
For good reason!

393
00:21:15,817 --> 00:21:20,239
Well, hell's bells, if
it ain't Felony Melanie.

394
00:21:20,322 --> 00:21:22,407
Wade!

395
00:21:22,491 --> 00:21:26,620
Hot damn, girl,
do we miss you around here!

396
00:21:26,703 --> 00:21:29,122
Hey, I think I saw poor, old
Fuzz just the other day.

397
00:21:29,164 --> 00:21:30,832
Oh, God,
you had to bring that up.

398
00:21:30,916 --> 00:21:32,626
I can't believe
you're the sheriff!

399
00:21:32,668 --> 00:21:34,670
Yep, I get to frisk pretty
little things like you all day

400
00:21:34,711 --> 00:21:36,255
and get paid for it.

401
00:21:36,338 --> 00:21:38,173
Wade, can you try and be
a little more professional?

402
00:21:38,257 --> 00:21:39,758
We got us a crime suspect here.

403
00:21:39,842 --> 00:21:42,928
Now, Melanie, you can't just go
breaking into people's houses.

404
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:46,014
I didn't break in, Wade.
I used a key...

405
00:21:46,098 --> 00:21:47,266
my key.

406
00:21:49,309 --> 00:21:51,019
Well, it still ain't
your house, darlin'.

407
00:21:51,103 --> 00:21:52,521
I'm gonna have to
escort you out.

408
00:21:52,604 --> 00:21:54,356
Use the cuffs, Wade, please?

409
00:21:54,439 --> 00:21:57,609
If you get him to sign these,
I'll let you run me out of town.

410
00:21:57,693 --> 00:21:58,819
Now, that's none
of your concern.

411
00:21:58,861 --> 00:22:00,445
Well, what do we got here?

412
00:22:03,365 --> 00:22:06,285
...A bill of divorcement?
...Mm-hmm.

413
00:22:06,368 --> 00:22:08,370
Hell, boy, I thought you said
you took care of this.

414
00:22:08,453 --> 00:22:09,705
And I thought I had.

415
00:22:09,788 --> 00:22:11,164
Obviously not.

416
00:22:11,248 --> 00:22:13,500
Well, if you two are still
married, it's her house, too.

417
00:22:13,542 --> 00:22:16,170
This here ain't nothin'
but a domestic dispute.

418
00:22:16,211 --> 00:22:18,005
He didn't hit you, did he?

419
00:22:18,046 --> 00:22:21,049
If he took a swing at you,
I'll take him in right now.

420
00:22:21,091 --> 00:22:23,177
We take that stuff
pretty serious nowadays.

421
00:22:27,556 --> 00:22:30,559
No, Wade,
Jake's never hit me.

422
00:22:30,642 --> 00:22:32,853
You know what?

423
00:22:32,895 --> 00:22:35,230
I don't have a single
childhood memory

424
00:22:35,314 --> 00:22:37,357
that doesn't have
you two in it.

425
00:22:37,399 --> 00:22:40,402
And that includes the night
I lit my ass on fire. Remember?

426
00:22:40,444 --> 00:22:41,361
Wade...

427
00:22:41,445 --> 00:22:44,323
Memory Lane is closed.

428
00:22:44,406 --> 00:22:48,035
Ah, boy, you two got a whole lot
of catchin' up to do...

429
00:22:48,076 --> 00:22:49,995
so I'm just gonna
leave you to it.

430
00:22:50,078 --> 00:22:51,830
Man, I set you up with
your wife. You owe me one!

431
00:22:51,914 --> 00:22:53,207
Why won't you just
sign the papers?!

432
00:22:53,290 --> 00:22:54,708
Hey, there is
nothin' I can do.

433
00:22:54,750 --> 00:22:58,921
The law is the law,
and she has done nothin' wrong.

434
00:22:59,004 --> 00:23:01,507
I suppose shoplifting steaks
at Winn-Dixie's okay.

435
00:23:01,590 --> 00:23:04,218
Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh! Oh!

436
00:23:04,301 --> 00:23:05,886
I took 'em back,
and you know it!

437
00:23:05,969 --> 00:23:09,264
You remember that vandalism out
at the stockyard? Totally her!

438
00:23:09,348 --> 00:23:11,558
Like I could tip a cow
by myself.

439
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:12,893
Hmm.

440
00:23:12,976 --> 00:23:16,688
Wade... isn't there
some outstanding warrant

441
00:23:16,772 --> 00:23:19,441
for whoever dumped your mama's
tractor in the fishpond?

442
00:23:19,525 --> 00:23:20,526
[Gasps]

443
00:23:20,609 --> 00:23:23,070
[Sighs deeply]

444
00:23:26,532 --> 00:23:28,575
We only have 10 of these, and
it's gonna be gone for good.

445
00:23:28,659 --> 00:23:30,786
So if you are loving
this monster...

446
00:23:30,869 --> 00:23:33,580
...[Snoring]
...[Telephone rings]

447
00:23:33,664 --> 00:23:35,249
We have eight only?

448
00:23:35,290 --> 00:23:37,501
If I knew how to say that in
Italian, I would, but I don't.

449
00:23:37,584 --> 00:23:39,211
Um, if you love this...

450
00:23:39,294 --> 00:23:42,422
9: 15? Honestly.

451
00:23:42,506 --> 00:23:44,424
Who could be callin'
at this hour?

452
00:23:45,133 --> 00:23:46,760
Hello?

453
00:23:46,844 --> 00:23:48,470
Hel-lo?

454
00:23:48,554 --> 00:23:50,597
Melanie: Hey, Mama.

455
00:23:50,681 --> 00:23:52,808
Melanie? Is that you?

456
00:23:52,891 --> 00:23:54,852
Oh, it's so late.
Are you all right?

457
00:23:54,935 --> 00:23:57,896
I, uh... um...

458
00:23:57,980 --> 00:23:59,898
I just thought
I'd surprise you.

459
00:23:59,982 --> 00:24:03,402
Well, this certainly is a fine
surprise, hearing from you...

460
00:24:03,485 --> 00:24:05,988
you know,
being such a busy girl and all.

461
00:24:06,071 --> 00:24:07,739
Of course, I call people

462
00:24:07,823 --> 00:24:10,909
while I'm doin' the dishes
or shellin' peas.

463
00:24:10,993 --> 00:24:13,996
Oprah calls it
"multitasking."

464
00:24:14,079 --> 00:24:16,748
Mama, the call
isn't the surprise.

465
00:24:16,832 --> 00:24:17,916
l-I'm in town.

466
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,294
Oh, Lord, love a duck!
Ha!

467
00:24:20,377 --> 00:24:23,630
Oh, my baby girl
has finally come home.

468
00:24:23,672 --> 00:24:25,340
Earl, she's in town.

469
00:24:25,424 --> 00:24:27,217
Earl: You gonna repeat
everything she says?

470
00:24:27,301 --> 00:24:29,469
...If you are, get off my chair.
...Mama...

471
00:24:29,553 --> 00:24:31,221
I'm just sittin' here, is all.

472
00:24:31,305 --> 00:24:32,639
What happened to the sound?

473
00:24:32,723 --> 00:24:35,225
I turned it down
so I could hear the phone ring.

474
00:24:35,309 --> 00:24:37,477
...Mama!
...What, are you a clairvoyant?

475
00:24:37,561 --> 00:24:39,605
It was so loud,
I couldn't hear myself think.

476
00:24:39,688 --> 00:24:42,941
...Mama...
...They could have heard it
at Joe and Lurlynn's house.

477
00:24:43,025 --> 00:24:44,776
...Hello?
...I only get 3 minutes.

478
00:24:44,860 --> 00:24:47,988
Oh, honey, you didn't need
to call, then. Just come on by.

479
00:24:48,030 --> 00:24:50,157
Uh... well, that's the thing.

480
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:53,619
I was sorta hoping
Daddy could come get me.

481
00:24:56,705 --> 00:24:59,541
Earl: So, what put you
in jail this time?

482
00:24:59,625 --> 00:25:02,544
Melanie: Jake and
his big, fat mouth.

483
00:25:02,586 --> 00:25:05,672
It's just a misunderstanding,
that's all.

484
00:25:05,714 --> 00:25:07,799
Yeah, kinda like that
weddin' I paid for, huh?

485
00:25:07,883 --> 00:25:10,135
I would hardly call that
a wedding.

486
00:25:10,219 --> 00:25:11,512
Boy was nervous.

487
00:25:11,553 --> 00:25:14,806
He was still drunk
from the night before.

488
00:25:14,890 --> 00:25:16,308
Can you blame him?

489
00:25:16,391 --> 00:25:18,227
Yes, I can!

490
00:25:18,310 --> 00:25:20,479
I went to the reception
by myself with puke

491
00:25:20,562 --> 00:25:23,565
all down my dress while he slept
it off in the Travelodge,

492
00:25:23,649 --> 00:25:25,526
and you're still
siding with that...

493
00:25:25,567 --> 00:25:27,611
I'm not sidin' with anybody.

494
00:25:27,694 --> 00:25:28,779
...[Sighs]
...[Sighs]

495
00:25:28,862 --> 00:25:30,030
The boy's changed, is all.

496
00:25:30,113 --> 00:25:32,282
Can we just
not talk about Jake, okay?

497
00:25:32,366 --> 00:25:35,035
l-I know he's the son you never
had, but I'm your only daughter,

