How deep is that water?

995
00:49:42,816 --> 00:49:43,901
About 8 feet.

996
00:49:43,984 --> 00:49:45,402
[Bryant groans]

997
00:49:48,947 --> 00:49:52,993
Look, Mel...
I signed your papers.

998
00:49:55,704 --> 00:49:57,748
Jake, I never
meant to hurt you,

999
00:49:57,831 --> 00:49:59,833
or anybody else,
for that matter.

1000
00:49:59,917 --> 00:50:03,420
And I just came out
here to say...

1001
00:50:03,504 --> 00:50:05,172
thank you.

1002
00:50:07,758 --> 00:50:10,802
You might want to find yourself
a place out of the way.

1003
00:50:12,888 --> 00:50:14,181
You can't just leave!

1004
00:50:14,264 --> 00:50:15,849
[Chuckles]

1005
00:50:15,933 --> 00:50:18,185
Sure I can.

1006
00:50:18,268 --> 00:50:19,770
You want to come?

1007
00:50:21,605 --> 00:50:22,689
Where you goin'?

1008
00:50:22,773 --> 00:50:24,858
Well...

1009
00:50:27,861 --> 00:50:29,696
I want to show you
somethin'.

1010
00:50:32,741 --> 00:50:34,201
I can't.

1011
00:50:36,161 --> 00:50:37,579
Can't or won't?

1012
00:50:38,997 --> 00:50:40,290
Both.

1013
00:50:40,374 --> 00:50:43,043
The girl I knew
used to be fearless.

1014
00:50:43,126 --> 00:50:44,878
The girl you knew
didn't have a life.

1015
00:50:44,962 --> 00:50:49,800
Well, I... guess you better
get on with it, then.

1016
00:50:49,883 --> 00:50:51,218
Come on, Bryant!

1017
00:50:53,262 --> 00:50:56,390
Come on, boy,
get in here.

1018
00:51:10,279 --> 00:51:12,906
E-Excuse me, do you know
Bobby Ray Bailey's address?

1019
00:51:12,948 --> 00:51:15,742
8 13 Lafayette.

1020
00:51:18,287 --> 00:51:20,122
You don't remember me,
do you?

1021
00:51:20,205 --> 00:51:22,666
Oh, I remember you
just fine.

1022
00:51:22,749 --> 00:51:25,919
You used to steal
catfish from my pond.

1023
00:51:27,713 --> 00:51:29,715
Yes, sir.

1024
00:51:29,798 --> 00:51:32,050
I did that.

1025
00:51:32,134 --> 00:51:33,760
I'm sorry.

1026
00:51:35,804 --> 00:51:37,181
'Course, on the weekends,

1027
00:51:37,264 --> 00:51:40,225
Bobby Ray goes over to
the Carmichael plantation...

1028
00:51:40,309 --> 00:51:41,894
visits with Colonel Murphy...

1029
00:51:41,977 --> 00:51:43,896
it being tourist
season and all.

1030
00:51:43,979 --> 00:51:45,147
Thank you.

1031
00:51:46,815 --> 00:51:49,067
[Birds chirping,
dog barking]

1032
00:51:57,743 --> 00:51:58,619
Yes?

1033
00:51:58,702 --> 00:52:01,622
Oh, hi! [Chuckles]
I'm Melanie Carmi...

1034
00:52:01,705 --> 00:52:05,876
um, um, Melanie Smooter.

1035
00:52:05,959 --> 00:52:07,794
I'm... I'm here
to see Bobby Ray.

1036
00:52:07,878 --> 00:52:08,879
[Cannon fires]

1037
00:52:08,962 --> 00:52:10,172
...Oh.
...Yee-haw!

1038
00:52:10,255 --> 00:52:12,633
If he's alive,
he's out back.

1039
00:52:12,674 --> 00:52:14,468
Come on.

1040
00:52:15,886 --> 00:52:18,805
They're out here somewhere.
Watch your step.

1041
00:52:25,687 --> 00:52:26,813
Bobby Ray?

1042
00:52:26,897 --> 00:52:28,899
Bobby Ray: Melanie?!

1043
00:52:28,982 --> 00:52:30,484
Don't move!

1044
00:52:30,567 --> 00:52:32,819
Yee-haw!

1045
00:52:32,861 --> 00:52:34,655
[Cannonball whirring]

1046
00:52:38,325 --> 00:52:40,160
Hot damn!

1047
00:52:40,202 --> 00:52:42,829
Hold your fire, sir.
I'll be right back.

1048
00:52:47,209 --> 00:52:49,002
We weren't aimin' for ya,

1049
00:52:49,044 --> 00:52:51,463
but I doubt I would have
gone to your funeral.

1050
00:52:54,216 --> 00:52:57,553
I guess I wouldn't blame you.

1051
00:53:01,598 --> 00:53:04,768
Forgotten how beautiful
this place was.

1052
00:53:04,852 --> 00:53:08,063
Guess it doesn't take much
to forget a lot of things.

1053
00:53:08,146 --> 00:53:10,440
Bobby Ray,
it's not like that.

1054
00:53:10,524 --> 00:53:12,985
You know what? I'll tell
you what it's not like.

1055
00:53:13,068 --> 00:53:16,697
It's not like Jake's the only
one that you run out on.

1056
00:53:19,199 --> 00:53:21,368
I'm so sorry I outed you.

1057
00:53:23,245 --> 00:53:25,914
I guess I figured
if I was pointing at you,

1058
00:53:25,998 --> 00:53:30,085
then... nobody would
see through me.

1059
00:53:30,169 --> 00:53:34,464
Bobby Ray,
I can't find the fuse!

1060
00:53:40,095 --> 00:53:42,723
I should go
before he kills himself.

1061
00:53:50,355 --> 00:53:52,482
Bye.

1062
00:54:04,286 --> 00:54:05,913
Afternoon.

1063
00:54:05,954 --> 00:54:07,581
Can I help you?

1064
00:54:07,623 --> 00:54:09,625
Barry Lowenstein,
"New York Post."

1065
00:54:09,708 --> 00:54:13,629
Ho-ho, boy,
am I glad to see you.

1066
00:54:13,712 --> 00:54:15,088
I'll tell you, it's, uh...

1067
00:54:15,130 --> 00:54:19,259
definitely, uh,
another world down here.

1068
00:54:19,343 --> 00:54:20,928
Uh, did you say
the "Post"?

1069
00:54:21,011 --> 00:54:22,471
Yes, I did.
l-I was hoping

1070
00:54:22,554 --> 00:54:24,389
to get an interview
with you and your family...

1071
00:54:24,473 --> 00:54:27,267
maybe, um, a few pictures
if you don't mind?

1072
00:54:27,309 --> 00:54:30,187
No.
I mean, uh, yes, I do...

1073
00:54:30,270 --> 00:54:31,188
mind.

1074
00:54:31,271 --> 00:54:32,481
They're not here.

1075
00:54:32,564 --> 00:54:34,733
Oh... wow.

1076
00:54:34,816 --> 00:54:36,818
This is just
as you described it.

1077
00:54:36,902 --> 00:54:40,697
It must have been amazing,
huh, growing up here?

1078
00:54:40,781 --> 00:54:42,449
Like a fantasy.

1079
00:54:42,533 --> 00:54:46,203
Would you mind if I take
a quick look inside?

1080
00:54:46,286 --> 00:54:47,704
Actually,
I'm on my way out.

1081
00:54:47,788 --> 00:54:49,623
I'll come back, then.

1082
00:54:49,665 --> 00:54:51,542
Uh, uh, okay,
but just a peek.

1083
00:54:51,625 --> 00:54:52,626
[Chuckles]

1084
00:54:55,128 --> 00:54:57,464
This is it...
home sweet home.

1085
00:54:57,548 --> 00:54:58,799
Wow!

1086
00:54:58,841 --> 00:55:00,509
How old is this place?

1087
00:55:00,592 --> 00:55:01,885
Uh...

1088
00:55:01,969 --> 00:55:06,181
it was built by my, uh,
great-great-great-grandfather,

1089
00:55:06,265 --> 00:55:07,808
Charles Carmichael,
in 1853.

1090
00:55:07,891 --> 00:55:11,728
Oh, boy, I bet you slid down
this banister a time or two.

1091
00:55:11,812 --> 00:55:12,771
Oh.

1092
00:55:12,855 --> 00:55:17,025
And over here we have
the, um...

1093
00:55:17,109 --> 00:55:19,486
[Maid humming]

1094
00:55:19,528 --> 00:55:21,989
...kitchen, but who hasn't
seen one of those?

1095
00:55:22,030 --> 00:55:23,156
Let's start over here.

1096
00:55:25,868 --> 00:55:27,703
[Door knob rattles]

1097
00:55:28,579 --> 00:55:29,913
[Humming continues]

1098
00:55:29,997 --> 00:55:31,498
[Gasps] Oh.

1099
00:55:32,916 --> 00:55:35,210
[Humming continues]

1100
00:55:38,046 --> 00:55:39,882
[Whispering] Now, this is
my favorite room.

1101
00:55:39,965 --> 00:55:44,928
It was part of the, um,
Underground Railroad.

1102
00:55:45,012 --> 00:55:47,431
[Whispering]
Why are we whispering?

1103
00:55:47,514 --> 00:55:50,309
The whole place
is haunted...

1104
00:55:50,392 --> 00:55:55,647
by ghosts of, um,
the Civil War soldiers.

1105
00:55:57,983 --> 00:56:00,402
[Door hinges creak]

1106
00:56:02,779 --> 00:56:05,199
[Creaking]

1107
00:56:07,201 --> 00:56:11,288
Jake! [Muttering]
...buttons.

1108
00:56:11,371 --> 00:56:13,916
No wonder we lost the war.

1109
00:56:15,751 --> 00:56:18,295
Was that one of 'em?

1110
00:56:18,378 --> 00:56:21,215
Melanie?

1111
00:56:21,256 --> 00:56:23,884
What are you doin'
in a closet?

1112
00:56:23,926 --> 00:56:26,428
Hi. Barry Lowenstein,
"New York Post."

1113
00:56:26,470 --> 00:56:29,723
Miss Carmichael is just showing
me around the plantation.

1114
00:56:31,934 --> 00:56:35,229
Uh, Mr. Lowenstein is writing
a piece on the family,

1115
00:56:35,270 --> 00:56:38,524
you know, since I'm marrying
the mayor's son and all.

1116
00:56:38,607 --> 00:56:41,235
I had no idea.
Isn't that something?

1117
00:56:42,778 --> 00:56:44,112
Yeah.

1118
00:56:46,490 --> 00:56:49,451
Well, a plantation by any
other name is just a farm.

1119
00:56:49,535 --> 00:56:51,870
But it does roll off the tongue
a little sweeter, doesn't it?

1120
00:56:51,954 --> 00:56:53,080
Huh.

1121
00:56:53,163 --> 00:56:57,167
Well, I do believe Miss Melanie
forgot her manners.

1122
00:56:57,251 --> 00:57:00,087
I'm Bobby Ray...
her cousin.

1123
00:57:00,128 --> 00:57:02,130
[Sighs]

1124
00:57:02,214 --> 00:57:03,590
Charmed.

1125
00:57:06,760 --> 00:57:09,137
See, when the Yankees
marched through Alabama,

1126
00:57:09,221 --> 00:57:11,890
they tried to destroy
our metal-formin' capabilities

1127
00:57:11,974 --> 00:57:14,601
by placin' barrels of powder
underneath the anvils.

1128
00:57:14,643 --> 00:57:16,436
Of course,
all that managed to do

1129
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:18,647
was blow 'em sky-high
for a few seconds.

1130
00:57:18,730 --> 00:57:21,316
So... in honor
of that act of stupidity,

1131
00:57:21,400 --> 00:57:25,279
we all... we get together to
re-create it for the tourists.

1132
00:57:33,120 --> 00:57:34,830
...[Cannon fires]
...Aah!

1133
00:57:34,913 --> 00:57:37,416
...Yee-haw!
...What the hell was that?!

1134
00:57:37,499 --> 00:57:38,458
[Cannonball whirring]

1135
00:57:38,500 --> 00:57:41,378
Hey, Grandpa!
This here's Barry!

1136
00:57:41,461 --> 00:57:44,047
He's doin' an article
on Melanie's weddin'!

1137
00:57:44,131 --> 00:57:47,134
Never heard of her.

1138
00:57:55,559 --> 00:57:57,352
Thanks!

1139
00:57:57,436 --> 00:58:00,689
[Tires screeching]

1140
00:58:00,772 --> 00:58:04,985
Well, aren't you
just a big, fat liar.

1141
00:58:05,068 --> 00:58:07,029
Bobby Ray!

1142
00:58:07,112 --> 00:58:08,488
Oh, go back to New York.

1143
00:58:08,572 --> 00:58:09,823
[Both laugh]

1144
00:58:14,036 --> 00:58:17,956
# If fear's
what makes us decide #

1145
00:58:18,040 --> 00:58:22,169
# Our future journey #

1146
00:58:22,211 --> 00:58:25,005
# Well, I'm not along
for a life #

1147
00:58:25,047 --> 00:58:26,715
# I'm not along for a life #

1148
00:58:26,798 --> 00:58:28,967
# 'Cause I'm still yearning #

1149
00:58:29,051 --> 00:58:34,932
# l-l-I am falling down #

1150
00:58:35,015 --> 00:58:37,267
# Try and stop me #

1151
00:58:37,351 --> 00:58:43,023
# It feels so good
to hit the ground #

1152
00:58:43,106 --> 00:58:45,400
# You can watch me #

1153
00:58:45,484 --> 00:58:48,362
# I fall right on my face #

1154
00:58:48,445 --> 00:58:53,158
# It's an uphill human race #

1155
00:58:53,242 --> 00:58:58,580
# And l-I am falling down #

1156
00:58:58,664 --> 00:59:01,583
Hmm. Hello.

1157
00:59:01,667 --> 00:59:04,086
I'm sorry about what I said.

1158
00:59:04,169 --> 00:59:05,462
Really sorry.

1159
00:59:05,546 --> 00:59:07,714
Melanie, forget it.

1160
00:59:07,798 --> 00:59:10,092
Boy:
She was not sharing.

1161
00:59:10,175 --> 00:59:13,387
Okay, y'all, you need
to eat and be quiet.

1162
00:59:13,470 --> 00:59:15,264
We're gonna have us
a little visit.

1163
00:59:15,347 --> 00:59:17,099
# Ye-a, ye-a, ye-a, yeah #

1164
00:59:17,182 --> 00:59:23,897
# Oh, l-l-I am falling down #

1165
00:59:23,939 --> 00:59:26,358
# Try and stop me #

1166
00:59:26,441 --> 00:59:29,403
# It feels so good
to hit the ground #

1167
00:59:29,444 --> 00:59:32,781
You know, he went up there.

1168
00:59:32,865 --> 00:59:35,242
Who?

1169
00:59:35,325 --> 00:59:38,078
Jake? When?

1170
00:59:38,120 --> 00:59:41,331
About a year after you left.

1171
00:59:41,415 --> 00:59:45,085
He doesn't know I know,
but Clinton let it slip once.

1172
00:59:45,169 --> 00:59:46,670
Jake was in New York?

1173
00:59:46,753 --> 00:59:48,630
He told Clinton he'd never
seen anything like it.

1174
00:59:48,714 --> 00:59:50,424
He realized straight off

1175
00:59:50,465 --> 00:59:54,428
he'd need more than
an apology to win you back.

1176
00:59:54,511 --> 00:59:58,265
He needed to conquer
the world first.

1177
00:59:58,348 --> 01:00:00,142
He's been tryin' ever since.

1178
01:00:00,225 --> 01:00:03,437
That's why he kept
sending the papers back.

1179
01:00:03,478 --> 01:00:05,731
Yeah.

1180
01:00:05,814 --> 01:00:10,444
Hmm. It's funny
how things don't work out.

1181
01:00:10,527 --> 01:00:11,445
[Baby gurgles]

1182
01:00:11,528 --> 01:00:14,281
It's funny how they do.

1183
01:00:21,622 --> 01:00:23,582
[Cheers and applause]

1184
01:00:31,507 --> 01:00:33,008
# Now, listen here #

1185
01:00:33,091 --> 01:00:36,303
# Well, I tried to tell you,
baby #

1186
01:00:36,345 --> 01:00:38,764
# But that don't make
no sense #

1187
01:00:38,847 --> 01:00:42,226
# Now you got me, baby #

1188
01:00:42,309 --> 01:00:44,144
# Up against that fence #

1189
01:00:44,228 --> 01:00:48,815
...# Ain't that a shame? #
...# Shame #

1190
01:00:48,899 --> 01:00:51,026
# Shame, shame
the way you do #

1191
01:00:51,109 --> 01:00:53,820
Man: Ha-ha! Ha!

1192
01:00:56,406 --> 01:00:59,535
Hey, look who I found
hangin' out by the parkin' lot.

1193
01:00:59,618 --> 01:01:01,036
Hesitant to join us.

1194
01:01:01,119 --> 01:01:03,247
# Shame, shame,
shame on you #

1195
01:01:03,330 --> 01:01:05,290
Jake: Anybody think
of anything in here

1196
01:01:05,374 --> 01:01:07,668
that, uh, might bother
Bobby Ray?

1197
01:01:07,709 --> 01:01:10,379
...Uh, Clinton's breath?
...Ha!

1198
01:01:12,172 --> 01:01:14,132
You still the same Bobby Ray
from last night?

1199
01:01:14,216 --> 01:01:16,343
Last time I checked,
yeah.

1200
01:01:16,426 --> 01:01:19,763
Well, then, I'm gonna
buy you a drink.

1201
01:01:19,847 --> 01:01:22,391
Well, you're really not
my type, I mean...

1202
01:01:22,474 --> 01:01:25,978
[Laughter]

1203
01:01:29,773 --> 01:01:32,442
Oh, honey, you...
you drink that from the top.

1204
01:01:32,526 --> 01:01:35,988
I'm just lookin' to see who
makes this Deep South Glass.

1205
01:01:36,071 --> 01:01:38,031
I wonder if you can get it
in New York.

1206
01:01:38,073 --> 01:01:39,283
It's beautiful.

1207
01:01:39,366 --> 01:01:41,910
Hey, Jake,
Mel would like to know

1208
01:01:41,994 --> 01:01:45,873
where she can find some of
that snooty-faluty glass.

1209
01:01:45,914 --> 01:01:47,416
Why ask me?

1210
01:01:47,457 --> 01:01:49,418
Oh, I don't know.
Maybe because you're...

1211
01:01:49,501 --> 01:01:50,711
[Clears throat]

1212
01:01:50,752 --> 01:01:53,881
You're all spiffed up
and... and all.

1213
01:01:53,922 --> 01:01:56,592
...["Sweet Home Alabama" plays]
...Am I missin' somethin'?

1214
01:01:56,675 --> 01:02:00,721
...[Cheering]
...Let's show some respect.

1215
01:02:08,937 --> 01:02:10,898
Jake...

1216
01:02:10,939 --> 01:02:13,442
When was the last time you
pushed me around the floor?

1217
01:02:13,483 --> 01:02:15,527
Clinton here has got
two left feet.

1218
01:02:15,611 --> 01:02:17,946
Well, Ms. Taylor,
I'd be honored.

1219
01:02:18,030 --> 01:02:19,656
Let's do it. Come on.

1220
01:02:19,740 --> 01:02:21,700
Come on, Mel,
get on out here!

1221
01:02:21,783 --> 01:02:25,746
Well, aren't you
the Lord of the Dance?

1222
01:02:25,829 --> 01:02:29,333
I ain't as clumsy as I look.
She just can't keep time.

1223
01:02:29,416 --> 01:02:31,627
You might have to
prove that to me.

1224
01:02:39,968 --> 01:02:41,762
Woman: Whoo!

1225
01:02:41,845 --> 01:02:44,681
# Now, I heard Mr. Young
sing about her #

1226
01:02:46,892 --> 01:02:49,603
You know, he's pretty good.
It might be you.

1227
01:02:49,686 --> 01:02:52,105
Oh, the hell you say.
Let me at him.

1228
01:02:52,147 --> 01:02:56,109
# I hope Neil Young
will remember #

1229
01:02:56,193 --> 01:02:58,654
Aw, look at them two
welded together.

1230
01:02:58,737 --> 01:03:01,990
Why do they fight it?

1231
01:03:02,074 --> 01:03:04,034
# Sweet home Alabama #

1232
01:03:04,117 --> 01:03:08,205
Maybe we could just talk.

1233
01:03:11,083 --> 01:03:14,044
# Sweet home Alabama #

1234
01:03:16,380 --> 01:03:18,882
# Lord, I'm comin' home
to you #

1235
01:03:21,885 --> 01:03:25,305
[Crickets chirping,
dog barking]

1236
01:03:25,347 --> 01:03:28,058
[Train whistle blows]

1237
01:03:28,141 --> 01:03:30,602
Come on, let's go
to the Roadhouse.

1238
01:03:30,686 --> 01:03:32,229
Nah.

1239
01:03:32,312 --> 01:03:36,525
What do you say we drive
out to Fairview and bowl?

1240
01:03:36,608 --> 01:03:37,985
I don't think so.

1241
01:03:38,026 --> 01:03:39,945
Do you want to go
harass somebody?

1242
01:03:40,028 --> 01:03:42,990
...[Chuckles]
...Unh-unh.

1243
01:03:43,031 --> 01:03:45,325
Hey, I know this great
place where we can...

1244
01:03:45,409 --> 01:03:46,410
All: No!

1245
01:03:52,791 --> 01:03:56,587
Y'all, I think I'm gonna
call it a night.

1246
01:03:59,590 --> 01:04:00,966
[Thud]

1247
01:04:01,049 --> 01:04:03,010
[Sighs]

1248
01:04:04,511 --> 01:04:08,849
[Crickets chirping]

1249
01:04:08,932 --> 01:04:11,727
[Indistinct shouting
in distance]

1250
01:04:35,542 --> 01:04:38,086
Hi, there, boy.

1251
01:04:38,170 --> 01:04:41,048
Sorry it took me so long.

1252
01:04:41,131 --> 01:04:45,177
I would have come sooner
if I'd known you were sick.

1253
01:04:48,764 --> 01:04:53,060
Actually, that's
probably not true.

1254
01:04:53,143 --> 01:04:57,314
[Exhales sharply]
I've been pretty selfish lately.

1255
01:04:59,733 --> 01:05:02,903
Dogs don't know anything
about that, do they, though?

1256
01:05:05,822 --> 01:05:09,117
You were always
like a big old pillow.

1257
01:05:13,080 --> 01:05:18,627
Like when everything
went pear-shaped...

1258
01:05:18,710 --> 01:05:22,089
[Voice breaking]
you never left my side.

1259
01:05:27,845 --> 01:05:30,597
And then I just left you.

1260
01:05:37,813 --> 01:05:41,942
[Crying] I bet you sat there
wondering what you'd done wrong.

1261
01:05:46,780 --> 01:05:49,700
I told him
it was my fault.

1262
01:05:51,618 --> 01:05:53,787
[Sighs]

1263
01:05:53,871 --> 01:05:56,039
[Sniffs]
Quit bein' so nice.

1264
01:05:56,123 --> 01:05:58,542
It's the truth.

1265
01:05:58,625 --> 01:06:01,503
How come it has to be
so complicated?

1266
01:06:01,587 --> 01:06:02,588
What?

1267
01:06:02,671 --> 01:06:04,131
Truth...

1268
01:06:04,214 --> 01:06:08,468
[Sniffs] life...

1269
01:06:08,552 --> 01:06:10,512
this.

1270
01:06:12,890 --> 01:06:14,975
He was one hell
of a good dog, wasn't he?

1271
01:06:15,058 --> 01:06:18,312
[Sighs, sniffs]
Yeah.

1272
01:06:18,395 --> 01:06:22,941
You looked like you were
having fun out there tonight.

1273
01:06:25,194 --> 01:06:28,197
I'm happy
in New York, Jake.

1274
01:06:28,238 --> 01:06:30,657
[Sighs]

1275
01:06:30,699 --> 01:06:34,745
But then I come down here
and...

1276
01:06:34,828 --> 01:06:36,747
this fits, too.

1277
01:06:36,830 --> 01:06:40,000
Since when does it have to be
one or the other?

1278
01:06:40,042 --> 01:06:42,669
You can have roots
and wings, Mel.

1279
01:06:45,464 --> 01:06:47,841
Maybe I could just fly south
for the winter.

1280
01:06:51,845 --> 01:06:53,680
Look.

1281
01:06:53,722 --> 01:06:55,516
What?

1282
01:06:55,599 --> 01:06:57,559
There.
Do you see 'em?

1283
01:07:01,563 --> 01:07:03,857
[Chuckles]
Lightning bugs?

1284
01:07:03,941 --> 01:07:06,193
Only you.
[Sniffs]

1285
01:07:06,276 --> 01:07:08,570
[Chuckles]

1286
01:07:08,654 --> 01:07:11,240
You know, I still go
out there sometimes.

1287
01:07:13,450 --> 01:07:16,495
I see those big thunderheads
rollin' in.

1288
01:07:18,205 --> 01:07:20,582
It's like a religion.
[Chuckles]

1289
01:07:20,666 --> 01:07:24,211
I had a dream about it
the other night.

1290
01:07:27,089 --> 01:07:29,216
You ever wonder
what would have happened

1291
01:07:29,299 --> 01:07:31,218
if we hadn't have gotten
pregnant?

1292
01:07:31,260 --> 01:07:32,845
Jake...

1293
01:07:32,928 --> 01:07:34,930
Just...

1294
01:07:35,013 --> 01:07:38,100
let me get this out
before I can't.

1295
01:07:39,935 --> 01:07:42,062
I thought that baby
would be an adventure.

1296
01:07:42,145 --> 01:07:45,899
And it took me a while
to realize

1297
01:07:45,983 --> 01:07:49,736
it would have been
your only adventure.

1298
01:07:49,778 --> 01:07:52,865
I just guess Mother Nature
knew better, huh?

1299
01:07:55,033 --> 01:07:57,953
I was so ashamed...

1300
01:08:00,289 --> 01:08:04,251
...'cause I felt...

1301
01:08:04,334 --> 01:08:07,004
relieved.

1302
01:08:09,506 --> 01:08:15,012
And all of a sudden, I just...
needed a different life.

1303
01:08:18,140 --> 01:08:22,394
You done real well
for yourself.

1304
01:08:22,477 --> 01:08:24,688
I'm proud of you, Mel.

1305
01:08:26,523 --> 01:08:30,277
I'm just sorry I never danced
with you at our weddin'.

1306
01:08:34,489 --> 01:08:38,327
I'm sure this next one's
gonna go better for ya.

1307
01:08:43,624 --> 01:08:45,792
Jake, I can't do this.

1308
01:08:45,834 --> 01:08:47,419
Hey...

1309
01:08:51,256 --> 01:08:54,551
I know.

1310
01:09:20,536 --> 01:09:22,204
Go home.

1311
01:09:35,843 --> 01:09:37,302
Well, I'm just sayin',
is all.

1312
01:09:37,386 --> 01:09:38,679
I mean, I... I saw

1313
01:09:38,720 --> 01:09:40,514
the way you two
were lookin' at each other.

1314
01:09:40,556 --> 01:09:42,474
Will you just shut up
about it, Mama?!

1315
01:09:42,558 --> 01:09:44,601
I can't help
the way Jake feels about me!

1316
01:09:44,685 --> 01:09:46,228
He hasn't done
anything wrong!

1317
01:09:46,311 --> 01:09:48,188
He hasn't done anything right
either!

1318
01:09:48,230 --> 01:09:50,190
I can't believe I'm even
having this argument!

1319
01:09:50,232 --> 01:09:52,192
I'm leaving! I'm gone!

1320
01:09:52,234 --> 01:09:53,694
I'm marrying another man!

1321
01:09:53,777 --> 01:09:56,905
Yes, that's right, you get
a second chance, so please

1322
01:09:56,989 --> 01:09:57,865
don't mess it up!

1323
01:09:57,948 --> 01:10:00,576
For who?
For me or for you?

1324
01:10:00,659 --> 01:10:01,869
Don't sass me, okay?

1325
01:10:01,952 --> 01:10:04,705
Don't you dare sass me,
'cause I have put up

1326
01:10:04,746 --> 01:10:06,874
with an awful lot from you
over the years.

1327
01:10:06,915 --> 01:10:09,918
Like what?! L-Like me quitting
your precious pageants?

1328
01:10:10,002 --> 01:10:13,046
I didn't want you to
end up like me! Damn it!

1329
01:10:13,130 --> 01:10:16,758
Now, you need to stay as far
away from here as you can.

1330
01:10:16,842 --> 01:10:18,385
That boy is quicksand.

1331
01:10:18,468 --> 01:10:21,805
What's so wrong
with being you, Mama?

1332
01:10:23,056 --> 01:10:26,810
I just think that you
deserve better, that's all.

1333
01:10:26,894 --> 01:10:29,730
I know you do.

1334
01:10:33,108 --> 01:10:35,402
You always have.

1335
01:10:35,444 --> 01:10:38,488
I'll see you in New York,
all right?

1336
01:10:38,572 --> 01:10:39,907
Mm-hmm.

1337
01:10:39,948 --> 01:10:42,242
You'll like it.

1338
01:10:42,284 --> 01:10:44,369
I promise.

1339
01:10:48,790 --> 01:10:51,168
Now, don't you forget to
say goodbye to your daddy.

1340
01:10:51,251 --> 01:10:52,711
[Drumroll]

1341
01:10:52,794 --> 01:10:54,004
...Fire!
...Fire!

1342
01:10:54,087 --> 01:10:55,631
...Fire!
...Fire!

1343
01:10:55,714 --> 01:10:56,673
Fire!

1344
01:11:06,600 --> 01:11:09,937
[Cannons fire]

1345
01:11:09,978 --> 01:11:12,231
Melanie: Daddy?

1346
01:11:14,316 --> 01:11:15,776
[Firing continues]

1347
01:11:15,859 --> 01:11:17,945
Daddy?

1348
01:11:24,576 --> 01:11:26,161
Daddy!

1349
01:11:26,245 --> 01:11:29,206
Who ya lookin' for,
darlin'?

1350
01:11:29,289 --> 01:11:31,458
Earl Smooter.

1351
01:11:31,542 --> 01:11:34,127
5th Regiment?

1352
01:11:34,211 --> 01:11:35,462
[All groaning]

1353
01:11:35,546 --> 01:11:37,464
Anybody seen Earl Smooter?

1354
01:11:37,548 --> 01:11:39,800
He's about to surrender!

1355
01:11:40,759 --> 01:11:41,844
Thank you!

1356
01:11:44,972 --> 01:11:46,890
[All sigh]

1357
01:11:46,974 --> 01:11:49,935
[Tires screech, horn honks]

1358
01:11:50,018 --> 01:11:51,436
After you.

1359
01:12:00,571 --> 01:12:01,738
Afternoon.

1360
01:12:01,822 --> 01:12:04,992
...How are ya?
...Good, thanks. Yourself?

1361
01:12:05,033 --> 01:12:07,870
No complaints.

1362
01:12:07,953 --> 01:12:09,830
That's a beautiful house.

1363
01:12:09,913 --> 01:12:12,374
Sure. Yeah.

1364
01:12:12,457 --> 01:12:15,544
You, uh, you here
to see Bobby Ray?

1365
01:12:15,627 --> 01:12:19,006
Actually, I'm, uh,
hoping to surprise Melanie.

1366
01:12:19,089 --> 01:12:22,843
...Melanie?
...My fiancee.

1367
01:12:22,926 --> 01:12:25,512
You got the wrong house,
don't ya?

1368
01:12:25,596 --> 01:12:29,433
This is, uh,
the Carmichael place, isn't it?

1369
01:12:30,517 --> 01:12:32,352
Are we talkin'
about the same girl?

1370
01:12:32,394 --> 01:12:33,979
...Melanie Smooter?
...Melanie Carmichael.

1371
01:12:34,062 --> 01:12:37,858
Oh, well,
that explains it.

1372
01:12:37,941 --> 01:12:40,360
That sure does.

1373
01:12:40,402 --> 01:12:42,613
Andrew Hennings.

1374
01:12:45,324 --> 01:12:47,075
Nice meeting you, Jake.

1375
01:12:47,159 --> 01:12:49,661
[Doorbell rings]

1376
01:12:59,463 --> 01:13:02,216
Hey, Jake.

1377
01:13:02,257 --> 01:13:03,926
What's goin' on?

1378
01:13:04,009 --> 01:13:05,385
Oh, you know,

1379
01:13:05,469 --> 01:13:09,264
I'm just, uh, talkin'
to Mel's fiance here.

1380
01:13:09,348 --> 01:13:11,767
Wonder if you might know
where she is.

1381
01:13:11,850 --> 01:13:13,644
Andrew Hennings.
You must be...

1382
01:13:13,727 --> 01:13:18,690
l-I'm Bobby Ray...
her, uh, cousin?

1383
01:13:18,774 --> 01:13:22,486
I see you've already met
Jake... her, uh...

1384
01:13:22,569 --> 01:13:24,530
...Other cousin.
...[Laughs]

1385
01:13:24,613 --> 01:13:27,282
Family! God, it's great
to meet you both.

1386
01:13:27,366 --> 01:13:29,284
I think Melanie said
somethin' last night

1387
01:13:29,368 --> 01:13:30,786
about, uh, visitin'
her daddy

1388
01:13:30,869 --> 01:13:32,579
u-up at the...
up at the battlefield.

1389
01:13:32,621 --> 01:13:34,915
...The battlefield?
...You know us Southerners.

1390
01:13:34,998 --> 01:13:36,583
I mean, the minute
the Confederacy died,

1391
01:13:36,667 --> 01:13:37,960
it became a moral issue.

1392
01:13:38,043 --> 01:13:42,256
Come on, I'll, uh, I'll
give you a ride up there.

1393
01:13:42,339 --> 01:13:45,259
That's great. Thank you.
All right. Nice meeting you.

1394
01:13:47,636 --> 01:13:52,766
# What this world needs
is a few more rednecks #

1395
01:13:52,808 --> 01:13:54,685
# So people ain't afraid
to take a stand #

1396
01:13:54,768 --> 01:13:58,772
So, who's...
Melanie... Smooter?

1397
01:13:58,856 --> 01:14:01,066
Local hero around here.

1398
01:14:01,149 --> 01:14:02,943
Why is that?

1399
01:14:02,985 --> 01:14:04,278
She blew up the bank.

1400
01:14:04,361 --> 01:14:06,613
And that made her a hero?

1401
01:14:06,697 --> 01:14:10,826
Well, notorious, anyway.
She was 10.

1402
01:14:10,909 --> 01:14:12,160
Oh.

1403
01:14:12,244 --> 01:14:16,456
Fortunately, nobody was hurt...
except, maybe, the cat.

1404
01:14:16,498 --> 01:14:18,667
What cat?

1405
01:14:18,750 --> 01:14:21,253
The one with the dynamite
on its back.

1406
01:14:21,336 --> 01:14:24,131
She blew up a cat?

1407
01:14:24,214 --> 01:14:26,550
...He was scheduled to die.
...From dynamite?

1408
01:14:26,633 --> 01:14:29,136
The vet said it had cancer,

1409
01:14:29,219 --> 01:14:32,181
so Eldon thought it'd be put
in one of those chambers,

1410
01:14:32,264 --> 01:14:34,933
you know, the ones
that suck their lungs out.

1411
01:14:35,017 --> 01:14:37,811
Little Mel, she couldn't bear
the thought of that.

1412
01:14:37,895 --> 01:14:40,314
She, uh, she wanted
somethin' more humane.

1413
01:14:40,397 --> 01:14:42,316
Yeah, sure.

1414
01:14:42,357 --> 01:14:45,527
So, they were doing some
blastin' out by the new highway.

1415
01:14:45,611 --> 01:14:48,697
So, we, uh, we took
old Fuzz up there,

1416
01:14:48,780 --> 01:14:50,157
taped him up.

1417
01:14:50,199 --> 01:14:53,702
Used about 30 feet of fuse
just to be on the safe side,

1418
01:14:53,785 --> 01:14:55,537
said our prayers,
and ran like hell.

1419
01:14:55,621 --> 01:14:57,497
Of course.

1420
01:14:57,581 --> 01:14:59,499
So, there we were,
sittin' in Virgie's Diner,

1421
01:14:59,541 --> 01:15:02,085
feelin' pretty blue.

1422
01:15:02,169 --> 01:15:04,171
When Mel looks up and sees
that damn cat,

1423
01:15:04,254 --> 01:15:07,382
trottin' down the road,
searchin' for Eldon.

1424
01:15:07,466 --> 01:15:09,843
No shit.

1425
01:15:09,885 --> 01:15:11,678
Yeah, and we
would have caught him, too,

1426
01:15:11,720 --> 01:15:14,932
but once that fuse hit his tail,
boom, he took off like a shot.

1427
01:15:15,015 --> 01:15:16,391
And into the bank.

1428
01:15:16,475 --> 01:15:19,019
Well... the theory is,

1429
01:15:19,102 --> 01:15:21,104
he probably wriggled loose
from the explosive.

1430
01:15:21,188 --> 01:15:24,566
'Cause, uh, people still
see him from time to time,

1431
01:15:24,650 --> 01:15:26,360
scorched tail and all.

1432
01:15:26,401 --> 01:15:29,696
He's a little skittish
around humans.

1433
01:15:29,738 --> 01:15:32,199
That's quite a story.

1434
01:15:32,241 --> 01:15:34,368
She was quite a girl.

1435
01:15:34,409 --> 01:15:37,287
# A little less talk
and a little more action #

1436
01:15:37,371 --> 01:15:39,289
Whatever happened to her?

1437
01:15:39,373 --> 01:15:40,707
# And a few more rednecks... #

1438
01:15:40,749 --> 01:15:44,002
Oh, you know...
wound up pregnant,

1439
01:15:44,086 --> 01:15:48,090
married some loser
right out of high school.

1440
01:15:48,173 --> 01:15:53,554
[Trumpet playing "Taps"]

1441
01:16:06,859 --> 01:16:08,193
["Taps" ends]

1442
01:16:08,277 --> 01:16:11,280
[Whistling,
cheers and applause]

1443
01:16:21,540 --> 01:16:24,001
Are you surprised?

1444
01:16:27,462 --> 01:16:29,298
What are you doing here?

1445
01:16:29,381 --> 01:16:31,508
Well, I came to deliver
your fiance.

1446
01:16:31,592 --> 01:16:32,843
I think
she was talking to me.

1447
01:16:32,926 --> 01:16:33,969
Jake...

1448
01:16:34,052 --> 01:16:35,679
Must be exhaustin'.

1449
01:16:35,762 --> 01:16:36,680
...What?
...What?

1450
01:16:36,763 --> 01:16:38,223
Livin' a lie.

1451
01:16:38,307 --> 01:16:39,516
What's he talking about?

1452
01:16:41,018 --> 01:16:43,979
You and I are in love
with two different people.

1453
01:16:49,902 --> 01:16:52,362
Is he a second cousin?

1454
01:16:53,488 --> 01:16:55,282
He's my husband.

1455
01:16:55,324 --> 01:16:56,491
Your what?

1456
01:16:56,575 --> 01:16:57,576
I mean my ex-husband.

1457
01:16:57,659 --> 01:16:59,119
You married your cousin?!

1458
01:16:59,203 --> 01:17:01,955
No, I came down here
to finalize my divorce.

1459
01:17:01,997 --> 01:17:04,499
Hey, darlin',
thought that was you.

1460
01:17:07,085 --> 01:17:08,795
Must be your new someone.

1461
01:17:10,380 --> 01:17:12,299
Earl Smooter...
glad to meet ya.

1462
01:17:16,178 --> 01:17:17,846
Melanie Smooter.

1463
01:17:20,682 --> 01:17:21,642
Andrew, wait.

1464
01:17:21,725 --> 01:17:23,310
Wait!

1465
01:17:23,393 --> 01:17:26,313
Andrew! Wait!

1466
01:17:26,396 --> 01:17:27,314
I just...

1467
01:17:27,397 --> 01:17:28,524
Please.

1468
01:17:28,607 --> 01:17:30,484
Let me try
and explain myself!

1469
01:17:30,526 --> 01:17:32,528
You don't understand!

1470
01:17:32,569 --> 01:17:34,988
This is not
who I am anymore!

1471
01:17:35,030 --> 01:17:37,032
Look, I don't know who you are
or what else you lied about,

1472
01:17:37,115 --> 01:17:38,534
but I know one thing...

1473
01:17:38,617 --> 01:17:42,246
there is a Lear Jet
in Mobile, and I am on it.

1474
01:17:44,289 --> 01:17:46,583
[Sighs]

1475
01:18:02,808 --> 01:18:04,184
I know you're thinkin'

1476
01:18:04,268 --> 01:18:07,020
I spoiled things good
this time.

1477
01:18:07,062 --> 01:18:10,774
Oh, hon, don't go accusin' me
of thinkin'.

1478
01:18:10,858 --> 01:18:13,986
I ain't done
anything of the sort.

1479
01:18:14,069 --> 01:18:17,030
Anyway, spoiled's in the eye
of the beholder...

1480
01:18:18,699 --> 01:18:20,158
...like these plums here.

1481
01:18:20,242 --> 01:18:24,037
Some people might
call them "spoiled"...

1482
01:18:24,079 --> 01:18:28,375
but I think that, um,
these almost-ruined ones

1483
01:18:28,417 --> 01:18:31,378
sometimes make
the sweetest jam.

1484
01:18:33,380 --> 01:18:35,257
Do you need any help?

1485
01:18:37,384 --> 01:18:38,969
It was kind of fun,

1486
01:18:39,052 --> 01:18:41,305
seeing Daddy up there,
surrendering.

1487
01:18:41,388 --> 01:18:43,348
Yeah.

1488
01:18:43,432 --> 01:18:46,226
He sure does have
a flair for the dramatic.

1489
01:18:46,268 --> 01:18:49,396
You certainly don't get it
from my side of the family.

1490
01:18:51,523 --> 01:18:53,358
Hey, y'all.

1491
01:18:53,442 --> 01:18:55,736
Look who I found
walkin' down l-58.

1492
01:18:55,819 --> 01:18:57,613
Hi.

1493
01:18:57,696 --> 01:19:00,532
Hi.

1494
